        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Bandwidth for sensitivity: The [CII] emission line was detected with Apex observations (Wagg et al. 2010, Figure 2 in proposal). The FWHM of the line is 340 km s^{-1}. We use that value to estimate the width of the line and therefore the bandwidth for the sentivity. For the line SPWs we request the FDM mode with a channel resolution of 976.5 kHZ, we want to recover all the velocity information posible. We note that the data rate is not a problem for this observations. If a lower data rate is requested by the system, we acould use the channel averaging function for the spectral setup up to N=8. For the continuum measurements we use the TDM mode with a channel resolution of 31.25 MHz.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Angular Resolution and Largest Angular Structure: The aim of our project is to compare the [CII] and continuum measurements with the VLA CO(2-1) maps of the same target. The resolution of the VLA maps is 0.2", we want to match the same resolution with the ALMA observations. Our CASA simulations reveal that with this resolution the extended emission can still be recovered. The largest Angular Structure is the size of the galaxy in the CO emission, which is of 0.7".</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Sensitivity: The requested rms of 0.17 mJy beam^{-1} is requested to get the detection of the weakest emiting clump in the CASA simulations (Figure 3 in the proposal) with at least 6 sigmas. The weakest clump has a flux density of ~1.0 mJy beam^{-1}. The brightest peak of the line emission will be detected with ~60 sigmas. For the continuum measurements, the weakest clump should be detected with 7 sigmas and the brightest peak with ~40 sigmas.

Bandwidth for sensitivity: The [CII] emission line was detected with Apex observations (Wagg et al. 2010, Figure 2 in proposal). The FWHM of the line is 340 km s^{-1}. We use that value to estimate the width of the line and therefore the bandwidth for the sentivity. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
    </prj:ScienceGoal>
